[src:opc-ua-deep/service-oriented-architecture] Service-oriented modeling is an SOA framework that identifies the various disciplines that guide SOA practitioners to conceptualize, analyze, design, and architect their service-oriented assets.
[src:opc-ua-deep/service-oriented-architecture] The Service-oriented modeling framework (SOMF) offers a modeling language and a work structure or "map" depicting the various components that contribute to a successful service-oriented modeling approach.
[src:opc-ua-deep/service-oriented-architecture] It illustrates the major elements that identify the "what to do" aspects of a service development scheme.
[src:opc-ua-deep/service-oriented-architecture] The model enables practitioners to craft a project plan and to identify the milestones of a service-oriented initiative.
[src:opc-ua-deep/service-oriented-architecture] SOMF also provides a common modeling notation to address alignment between business and IT organizations.
[src:opc-ua-deep/service-oriented-architecture] Some enterprise architects believe that SOA can help businesses respond more quickly and more cost-effectively to changing market conditions.
[src:opc-ua-deep/service-oriented-architecture] This style of *architecture* promotes reuse at the macro (service) level rather than micro (classes) level.
[src:opc-ua-deep/service-oriented-architecture] It can also simplify interconnection to—and usage of—existing IT (legacy) assets.
[src:opc-ua-deep/service-oriented-architecture] With SOA, the idea is that an organization can look at a problem holistically.
[src:opc-ua-deep/service-oriented-architecture] Theoretically there would not be a mass of developers using whatever tool sets might please them.
[src:opc-ua-deep/service-oriented-architecture] But rather they would be coding to a standard that is set within the business.
[src:opc-ua-deep/service-oriented-architecture] They can also develop enterprise-wide SOA that encapsulates a business-oriented infrastructure.
[src:opc-ua-deep/service-oriented-architecture] SOA has also been illustrated as a highway system providing efficiency for car drivers.
[src:opc-ua-deep/service-oriented-architecture] The point being that if everyone had a car, but there was no highway anywhere, things would be limited and disorganized, in any attempt to get anywhere quickly or efficiently.
[src:opc-ua-deep/service-oriented-architecture] IBM Vice President of Web Services Michael Liebow says that SOA "builds highways".
[src:opc-ua-deep/service-oriented-architecture] In some respects, SOA could be regarded as an architectural evolution rather than as a revolution.
[src:opc-ua-deep/service-oriented-architecture] It captures many of the best practices of previous software architectures.
