[src:opc-ua-deep/service-oriented-architecture] A service comprises a stand-alone unit of functionality available only via a formally defined interface.
[src:opc-ua-deep/service-oriented-architecture] Services can be some kind of "nano-enterprises" that are easy to produce and improve.
[src:opc-ua-deep/service-oriented-architecture] Also services can be "mega-corporations" constructed as the coordinated work of subordinate services.
[src:opc-ua-deep/service-oriented-architecture] Separation promotes the decoupling of services from consuming projects.
