[src:opc-ua-deep/service-oriented-architecture] Documentation and test artifacts of the service are not embedded within the detail of the larger project.
[src:opc-ua-deep/service-oriented-architecture] This is important when the service needs to be reused later.
[src:opc-ua-deep/service-oriented-architecture] SOA promises to simplify testing indirectly.
[src:opc-ua-deep/service-oriented-architecture] Services are autonomous, stateless, with fully documented interfaces, and separate from the cross-cutting concerns of the implementation.
[src:opc-ua-deep/service-oriented-architecture] If an organization possesses appropriately defined test data, then a corresponding stub is built that reacts to the test data when a service is being built.
