[src:opc-ua-deep/service-oriented-architecture] At the same time, emerging open-source XML parsing technologies (such as VTD-XML) and various XML-compatible binary formats promise to significantly improve SOA performance.
[src:opc-ua-deep/service-oriented-architecture] Stateful services require both the consumer and the provider to share the same consumer-specific context, which is either included in or referenced by messages exchanged between the provider and the consumer.
[src:opc-ua-deep/service-oriented-architecture] This constraint has the drawback that it could reduce the overall scalability of the service provider if the service-provider needs to retain the shared context for each consumer.
[src:opc-ua-deep/service-oriented-architecture] It also increases the coupling between a service provider and a consumer and makes switching service providers more difficult.
